text.tspan: When doing file management, there is nothing which is so horribly awkward to perform as moving multiple
files. To solve this, we can add the carefully named "Pile o' files".
The Pile o' files is the clipboard of Marlin. In it you can see which files you have currently copied or cut out.
If it isn't empty, it will show in the bottom of the windows, else it will pop up if you start dragging a file.
Small emblems show if the files are copied or cut out. Dragging files out of the pile will obviously paste/copy.
Right-clicking a file in the pile will give you the option to change action or restore the file to it's original state.
The Pile o' files can also be collapsed to preserve space. If there are no files in the pile, it will not show at all.
